subCards.title: Moana 2 - Official 'Big, Bad Matangi' Teaser Trailer
subCards.abstract: Check out this teaser trailer for Moana 2 to learn more about this upcoming Disney animated musical film. Walt Disney Animation Studios’ epic animated musical “Moana 2” reunites Moana (voice of Auli‘i Cravalho) and Maui (voice of Dwayne Johnson) three years later for an expansive new voyage alongside a crew of unlikely seafarers. After receiving an unexpected call from her wayfinding ancestors, Moana must journey to the far seas of Oceania and into dangerous, long-lost waters for an adventure unlike anything she’s ever faced. Directed by David Derrick Jr., Jason Hand and Dana Ledoux Miller, and produced by Christina Chen and Yvett Merino, “Moana 2” features music by Grammy winners Abigail Barlow and Emily Bear, Grammy nominee Opetaia Foa‘i, and three-time Grammy winner Mark Mancina. Jared Bush and Miller are writing the film, which is executive produced by Jennifer Lee, Bush and Johnson. The film also features returning stars Rachel House (Moana’s Grandma, Tala), Temuera Morrison (Moana’s father, Chief Tui) and Nicole Scherzinger (Moana’s mother, Sina), as well as the voices of Hualālai Chung, David Fane and Rose Matafeo as Moana’s new crew members Moni, Kele and Loto, respectively. Awhimai Fraser voices mysterious new character Matangi; Gerald Ramsey plays Moana’s ancestor, Tautai Vasa; and Khaleesi Lambert-Tsuda lends her voice to Moana’s adoring and adorable little sister, Simea.Disney's Moana 2 opens in theaters on November 27, 2024.

slides.body: Ancient Egyptian civilisation ended with a whimper back in 30 BCE when the Romans defeated Pharaoh Cleopatra and Egypt became part of the Roman Empire. slides.title: Archeologists make stunning finds in 4,000-year-old Egyptian tombs
slides.body: The tomb was found in the South Asasif necropolis, next to the Temple of Hatshepsut, along the west bank of the Nile River. It is known as the Karabasken (TT 391 tomb) as the South Asasif Conservation project looks to clear, restore, and reconstruct the three tombs of the Theban South Asasif necropolis. In tomb 391, the researchers found coffins for men, women and children dating back to the Middle Kingdom (1938 BCE–1630 BCE). Experts believe it was used as a family tomb for multiple generations from the 12th through the beginning of the 13th Dynasty (Picture: South Asasif Conservation project)

cards.title: 25 movies to watch before they leave Netflix this month
cards.abstract: Stacker compiled a list of movies leaving Netflix in November 2024, from a sports biopic to a star-studded rom-com.

slides.title: The movies leaving Netflix this month
slides.body:
When the clock strikes midnight after Halloween, a different holiday season kicks into high gear. The start of November instantly begins the countdowns to Thanksgiving, Christmas, Hanukkah, and Kwanzaa, with family gatherings, big meals, travel plans, and shopping sprees right around the corner. The two-month stretch can be a stressful one, but it doesn't have to be! At least, as long as you can block out the noise with some non-holiday movies—and there are some quality ones to catch before they leave Netflix at the end of November.

There are quite a few reasons a movie might leave Netflix; perhaps its rights are no longer available, or its popularity doesn't justify the cost to license it. Though the motivation may vary, 25 movies are leaving Netflix in November, so it's time to think twice about your viewing choices.

Let's be honest, it's a bit early to string up the lights and start baking sugar cookies. If you're still in the Halloween spirit and want to keep those pumpkins out on the front porch, Netflix has some spooky streaming options for you. "Evil Dead Rise," the fifth installment in the supernatural franchise, is hanging around Netflix until Nov. 22. Helmed by Lee Cronin, the 2023 film follows two estranged sisters who engage in a battle after an earthquake wakes up an ancient demon ready to possess any and everything. Before the month ends, you also have time to return to Derry, Maine, and join the now-adult Losers Club on a mission to get rid of Pennywise for good in 2019's "It Chapter Two."

Ahead of "Gladiator II" hitting theaters on Nov. 22, there are plenty of action-packed movies to get you in the mood for the historical epic's triumphant return. The obvious first choice is "Troy," a similar sword-and-sandals epic from 2004 starring Brad Pitt and Eric Bana that departs Netflix on Nov. 30. If you're looking for a bigger dose of adrenaline, try a couple of others: "Hunter Killer," a 2018 B-movie thriller starring everyman action hero Gerard Butler, this time as a submarine captain charged with rescuing the Russian president to avoid World War III; and "Point Break," the 2015 remake of the 1991 classic about an FBI agent who infiltrates a team of ex-athletes and their high-stakes corporate heists. Both will sign off from Netflix on Nov. 30.

That's not all, of course. There is also a sports biopic, a star-studded rom-com, an adult animated comedy, and many more making their last calls. But don't worry, Stacker compiled a list of all the films departing Netflix in November, along with the last day they'll be available to stream on the platform. There are also supplementary insights from IMDb on each movie's director, cast, and runtime. 

Take a look and start planning your movie nights now—they're the perfect getaway from the holiday hustle and bustle, and you don't even have to leave your couch.

slides.title: ‘God of chaos’ asteroid will transform as it skims past Earth
slides.body: A God of chaos asteroid is not going to hit Earth and end all life. Well, it is not predicted to hit Earth, so far. The 1,100-foot-long asteroid has been named after the Egyptian God of chaos, known as Apophis, and if anything, it will experience a chaotic change to its own landscape when it makes its close approach to Earth in 2029, a new study claims (Picture: Getty)

slides.body: A cult favorite, Little Miss Sunshine (2006) follows the dysfunctional Hoover family's comedic road trip to California. With an old van as their chariot, this quirky ensemble, including young Olive, her motivational-speaker father, and her volatile, foul-mouthed grandfather, head to a beauty pageant. slides.title: Thelma & Louise
slides.body: Released in 1991, Thelma & Louise is a classic of the genre. This iconic film starring Geena Davis and Susan Sarandon embeds feminist themes through an enthralling storyline of escape and self-discovery. What begins as an innocent getaway quickly spirals into a cross-country chase, cementing it as a cultural touchstone. More about Thelma & Louise

image.title: Thelma & Louise
image.caption:
In the iconic film "Thelma & Louise," these two strong women find themselves on a transformative journey after a tragic incident during their weekend getaway. As fugitives on the run, Louise shoots a man in defense of her friend Thelma after a near-rape encounter. Their cross-country escape reveals the resilience, courage, and depth of their friendship, turning their tumultuous escape into a profound exploration of freedom and self-discovery.
